Sasol and Mondi Shares May Be Active: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-07-27T22:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/sasol-mondi-may-be-active-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined 274.74, or 0.9
percent, to 31,593.99 by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL)  , the biggest producer of gas from coal,
said a strike of fuel petroleum workers had a negligible effect
on the company’s growth program. The shares dropped 6.45 rand,
or 1.8 percent, to 346.50 rand.  Mondi Ltd. (MND SJ), Europe’s largest maker of office
paper, releases an interim earnings for the six months ended
June 30. The shares gained 39 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 55.40
rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in  Cape Town  at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  